{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T18:03:50.130Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Maximum Likelihood Estimation (MLE)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the fundamental statistical method that finds the parameter values of a model which make the observed data most probable—it answers the question \"If my data came from this model, what parameter values make the data I observe most likely?\" and serves as the backbone of training for nearly all machine learning models, especially generative AI systems like language models, VAEs, and diffusion models."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Maximum Likelihood Estimation — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Core idea:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Maximum Likelihood Estimation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " selects values of model parameters that produce a distribution giving the observed data the greatest probability."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In other words:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\"If I observed this data, what parameter values are most likely to have generated it?\" [web:345]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mathematical definition:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For observed data "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "D = {x₁, x₂,..., xₙ}"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and model parameters "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "θ"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "θ_MLE = argmax L(θ | D)\n      = argmax log L(θ | D)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "L(θ | D)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = likelihood function = P(D | θ)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "argmax"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = value of θ that maximizes the function\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "θ"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "italic"}], "text": "MLE"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": " = Maximum Likelihood Estimate"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[www2.stat.duke](http://www2.stat.duke.edu/courses/Summer13/sta111.001-1/Calendar_files/Lecture22.pdf)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Intuitive meaning:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Imagine you observed coin flips: D = [heads, heads, tails]\n\nMLE asks: \"What coin bias θ is most likely to produce this data?\"\n\nθ = 0.1:  P(D|θ) = very small → unlikely to produce data\nθ = 0.5:  P(D|θ) = moderate → plausible\nθ = 0.7:  P(D|θ) = largest → most likely to produce data ✓\n\nMLE finds θ = 2/3 (the peak) [web:345][web:346]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"The MLE is the parameter point for which the observed sample is most likely\"."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The MLE algorithm — Step-by-step"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 1: Choose a probability model\n  Assume data comes from distribution with parameters θ\n  Example: xᵢ ~ Normal(μ, σ²) [web:345]\n\nStep 2: Write the likelihood function\n  L(θ | D) = P(x₁, x₂, ..., xₙ | θ)\n           = Πᵢ₌₁ᴺ P(xᵢ | θ) [product over all observations] [web:345][web:347]\n\nStep 3: Take the log-likelihood (for convenience)\n  log L(θ | D) = Σᵢ₌₁ᴺ log P(xᵢ | θ) [web:345][web:349]\n\nStep 4: Differentiate w.r.t. parameters\n  d/dθ [log L(θ | D)] [web:349]\n\nStep 5: Set to zero and solve\n  d/dθ [log L] = 0\n  Solve for θ [web:349]\n\nStep 6: Verify it's a maximum\n  Check second derivative: d²/dθ² [log L] < 0 [web:349]\n\nStep 7: θ_MLE = solution [web:345][web:349]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why log-likelihood?"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Log-likelihood is easier to optimize because:\n- Sums are easier to compute than products [web:345]\n- Prevents numerical underflow (multiplying many small probabilities)\n- Maximizing log-likelihood = maximizing likelihood (same θ)\n\nThe transformation from likelihood (L) to log-likelihood (log L) preserves the order of parameter values that maximize the function [web:349]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 1: Coin flip (Bernoulli) MLE"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Setup:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Data: D = [heads, heads, tails] (2 heads, 1 tail)\nParameter: θ = probability of heads\n\nModel: xᵢ ~ Bernoulli(θ)\nP(x|θ) = θ if x=heads, (1-θ) if x=tails"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MLE derivation:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 1: Likelihood\nL(θ | D) = θ × θ × (1 - θ)\n         = θ²(1 - θ) [web:345]\n\nStep 2: Log-likelihood\nlog L(θ | D) = log(θ²(1 - θ))\n             = 2 log(θ) + log(1 - θ) [web:345]\n\nStep 3: Differentiate\nd/dθ [log L] = 2/θ - 1/(1 - θ) [web:345]\n\nStep 4: Set to zero\n2/θ - 1/(1 - θ) = 0\n2(1 - θ) = θ\n2 - 2θ = θ\nθ = 2/3 [web:345]\n\nStep 5: θ_MLE = 2/3 ✓\n\nInterpretation: 2 heads out of 3 flips = 67% heads"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 2: Gaussian MLE"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Setup:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Data: D = {x₁, x₂, ..., xₙ}\nModel: xᵢ ~ Normal(μ, σ²)\nParameters: μ (mean), σ² (variance)\n\nP(x|μ,σ²) = (1/√(2πσ²)) × exp(-(x - μ)²/(2σ²))"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MLE for mean μ:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Log-likelihood:\nlog L = -N/2 log(2π) - N/2 log(σ²) - Σᵢₜ₁ᴺ (xᵢ - μ)²/(2σ²)\n\nDifferentiate w.r.t. μ:\nd/dμ [log L] = -Σᵢₜ₁ᴺ (xᵢ - μ)/(σ²) = 0\n\nSolve:\nΣᵢₜ₁ᴺ (xᵢ - μ) = 0\nΣᵢₜ₁ᴺ xᵢ - Nμ = 0\nμ_MLE = Σᵢₜ₁ᴺ xᵢ / N = sample mean ✓ [web:344]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MLE for variance σ²:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Differentiate w.r.t. σ²:\nd/dσ² [log L] = -N/(2σ²) + Σᵢₜ₁ᴺ (xᵢ - μ)²/(2σ⁴) = 0\n\nSolve:\nNσ² = Σᵢₜ₁ᴺ (xᵢ - μ)²\nσ²_MLE = Σᵢₜ₁ᴺ (xᵢ - μ_MLE)² / N = sample variance ✓ [web:344]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MLE as an optimization problem"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Finding the MLE is an optimization problem [web:344]\n\nWe want to find the parameter point for which the observed sample is most likely [web:344]\n\nThe mean at which the likelihood is largest is our estimate [web:346]\n\nIf we also want the standard deviation, we can repeat this idea by scanning over the standard deviation or searching over both the mean and standard deviation together to find the overall peak [web:346]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MLE in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why MLE is crucial:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MLE is a key building block in generative modeling [web:345]\n\nMaximum Likelihood Estimation (MLE) is a method to find the parameters of a model that make the observed data most probable [web:345]"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Generative Model"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How MLE applies"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Language Models (GPT)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Maximize likelihood of next tokens (equivalent to minimizing cross-entropy loss)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "VAEs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Approximate MLE by maximizing likelihood of data under latent distribution"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Diffusion Models"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Approximate MLE by learning to reverse diffusion process"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "GANs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Implicit MLE by matching generated distribution to real data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Regression"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Direct MLE (e.g., Gaussian → minimize MSE)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[medium](https://medium.com/@sudeepdc/maximum-likelihood-estimation-the-backbone-of-modern-ai-519e6936d300)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Language training example:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training GPT-4:\n\nData: Billions of text tokens \"the cat sat on the ___\" → \"mat\"\n\nMLE objective: Maximize P(\"mat\" | \"the cat sat on the\")\n\nCross-entropy loss = -log P(correct token)\n\nMinimizing cross-entropy = Maximizing likelihood [web:345]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"MLE helps learn the model parameters so the model can generate new data resembling the observed data\"."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MLE vs Bayesian Estimation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fundamental difference:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Maximum Likelihood (MLE)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bayesian Estimation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it finds"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single best θ: θ"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "MLE = argmax L(θ"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "D)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Full distribution: P(θ"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "D)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prior used"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No (ignores prior information)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes (incorporates prior knowledge)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Point estimate (one value)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Distribution (many values with probabilities)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Uncertainty"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not captured (single number)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fully captured (probability distribution)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "When best"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large datasets, no prior knowledge"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Small datasets, prior knowledge available"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[www2.stat.duke](https://www2.stat.duke.edu/courses/Summer13/sta111.001-2/Lectures_site/lec23_site.pdf)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bayes' Theorem relationship:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bayesian: P(θ|D) = P(D|θ) × P(θ) / P(D)\n          = likelihood × prior / normalization [web:344]\n\nMLE: θ_MLE = argmax P(D|θ)\n     = argmax likelihood (ignores prior) [web:344]\n\nMLE is equivalent to Bayesian with uniform prior (P(θ) = constant) [web:344]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key properties of MLE"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Consistent"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "As N → ∞, θ"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "MLE → true parameter value"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Efficient"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Achieves minimum variance among all estimators (asymptotically)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Unbiased (asymptotic)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "As N → ∞, E[θ"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "MLE] = true θ"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Invariant"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If θ̂ is MLE for θ, then g(θ̂) is MLE for g(θ)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Important"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": MLE is asymptotically optimal (works best with large data)."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common MLE formulas"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Distribution"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Parameter"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MLE formula"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bernoulli"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "p (probability)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "p_MLE = successes / N [e.g., 2/3 for 2H, 1T]"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gaussian"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "μ (mean)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "μ"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "MLE = sample mean = Σxᵢ/N"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gaussian"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "σ² (variance)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "σ²"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "MLE = sample variance = Σ(xᵢ - μ)²/N"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Poisson"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "λ (rate)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "λ"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "MLE = Σxᵢ/N = sample mean"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "MLE definition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": θ"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "MLE = argmax L(θ|D) = parameters that make data most probable"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Core question"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"What parameter values make the observed data most likely?\""}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Algorithm"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Choose model → write likelihood → take log → differentiate → set to zero → solve"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Log-likelihood"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": log L = Σ log P(xᵢ|θ) (easier than products)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Coin MLE"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": θ = heads/N (2/3 for 2H, 1T)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gaussian MLE"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": μ = sample mean, σ² = sample variance"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Finding MLE is an optimization problem (find peak of likelihood)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Language models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Cross-entropy loss = negative log-likelihood; minimizing CE = maximizing likelihood"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Generative AI"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": MLE is key building block for VAEs, GANs, diffusion models, language models"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "MLE vs Bayesian"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": MLE finds single best θ; Bayesian finds distribution P(θ|D)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No prior"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": MLE ignores prior information (uses only likelihood)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Consistent"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": As N → ∞, θ"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "MLE → true parameter"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Efficient"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Achieves minimum variance asymptotically"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large data"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": MLE works best with large datasets"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, Maximum Likelihood Estimation is absolutely fundamental: it's the primary objective for training language models like GPT (maximize likelihood of next tokens), VAEs (maximize likelihood under latent distribution), diffusion models (approximate MLE), and GANs (match distributions)—making it the statistical foundation that enables generative models to learn data distributions and generate realistic new samples; understanding MLE is essential for mastering how neural networks learn from data."}]}]}}